AILANG Compiler Quick Start Guide
Installation & Setup
1. Project Structure
AILANG/                     # Root directory
├── main.py                 # Compiler entry point
├── ailang_parser/          # Parser modules
├── ailang_compiler/        # Compiler modules
│   └── modules/           # Compiler components
├── test_*.ailang          # Test files
└── your_project.ailang    # Your code here
2. Basic Compilation
bash# Navigate to AILANG root directory
cd AILANG

# Compile a program
python3 main.py myprogram.ailang

# This creates myprogram_exec (executable)
./myprogram_exec
Compiler Options
Debug Levels
bashpython3 main.py myprogram.ailang        # Production build (no debug)
python3 main.py -D myprogram.ailang     # Debug level 1
python3 main.py -D2 myprogram.ailang    # Debug level 2 (verbose)
python3 main.py -D3 myprogram.ailang    # Debug level 3 (all debug)
VM Modes
bashpython3 main.py --vm-mode user myprogram.ailang    # User mode (default, safe)
python3 main.py --vm-mode kernel myprogram.ailang  # Kernel mode (privileged)
Custom Output
bashpython3 main.py -o myapp myprogram.ailang   # Creates 'myapp' instead of 'myprogram_exec'
Multiple Files
bashpython3 main.py file1.ailang file2.ailang file3.ailang  # Compile multiple files
Quick Examples
Hello World
ailang// hello.ailang
PrintMessage("Hello, AILANG!")
bashpython3 main.py hello.ailang
./hello_exec
With Debug
ailang// calc.ailang
x = 10
y = 20

Debug("values", level=1) {
    PrintMessage("Debug: x and y values")
    PrintNumber(x)
    PrintNumber(y)
}

result = Add(x, y)
PrintNumber(result)
bashpython3 main.py -D calc.ailang   # Shows debug output
python3 main.py calc.ailang      # No debug output
Project Organization
Recommended Structure
AILANG/
├── projects/
│   ├── calculator/
│   │   ├── calc.ailang
│   │   └── calc_lib.ailang
│   └── examples/
│       └── demos.ailang
└── tests/
    └── test_*.ailang
Workflow

Create your .ailang file in the AILANG root or a subdirectory
Compile with python3 main.py yourfile.ailang
Run the generated executable ./yourfile_exec
Use -D flags during development for debugging

Help
bashpython3 main.py -h    # Show all compiler options
Testing
bash# Run the test suite
./run_function_tests.sh
